    "created_at": "2014-10-16T17:10:21Z",
    "updated_at": "2014-10-16T17:10:21Z",
    "body": "I'm not sure I understand the use case for `lli` here.  You can't take bytecode from `rustc` that thinks it's targetting one platform and then compile/run it on another platform.  `size_of::<int>()` and processing of `#[cfg]` directives will be wrong, for example.  It may work in some limited cases but it's not really a safe or reasonable thing to do.\n\nSince you need to compile things differently for host vs. target, you might as well use the normal compilation path for both.\n",
