    "created_at": "2014-10-16T17:17:05Z",
    "updated_at": "2014-10-16T17:18:20Z",
    "body": "> It would be a better solution to build and install a rust-lli along with the compiler, at least until Rust can depend on a reasonably old stable version of the upstream LLVM.\n\nThis is already supported via the `--llvm-root` parameter for `configure`. The only things in Rust's fork of LLVM are a compile-time optimization and a `NullCheckElimination` pass. Both could probably be pushed upstream anyway.\n",
